SO, YOUR LIFE IS NOW A MOVIE. WHAT WOULD THE SOUNDTRACK BE?
So, here's how it works:
1. Open your library (iTunes, Winamp, Media Player, iPod, etc)
2. Put it on shuffle
3. Press play
4. For every question, type the song that's playing
5. When you go to a new question, press the next button
6. Don't lie and try to pretend you're cool...


Opening credits: "Weekend Warriors" -A Change of Pace

Waking up: "Wrong Way" -Sublime

First Day of school: "Don't Wanna Hurt You" -The Sounds

Falling in love: "New Hope" -Blink 182

First time Song: "Heart Attack" -Sum 41

Fight Song: "So-So Gigolo" -Cursive

Breaking up: "On Top" -The Killers

Prom: "A Goodnight's Sleep" -The Starting Line

Life: "Cable Car" -The Fray

Mental Breakdown: "Stop" -Plain White T's

Driving: "We Will Rock You" -Queen

Flashback: "The First Drop" -Rise Against

Getting Back together: "Boombox Generation" -MCS

Wedding: Incubus- "This Ride" -The Starting Line 

Birth of a child: "The Wicked End" -Avenged Sevenfold

Final Battle: "Autography" -The Starting Line (MORE...holy shit we can tell what my shuffle likes...)

Death scene: "Please Don't Do This" -PWT's

Funeral song: "Shut up" -Black Eyed Peas

End credits: "Down and Out" -TAI

AND the best part about it is that i have the worst dye job ever on top of that, so now i'm just a girl with ugly, ugly hair. I am so ridiculously bored. 
I'm babysitting on New Year's Eve, which is okay because i am making a shitload of money and that's good, BUT somehow i picked up an extra kid, and they were scared because they don't live here, and then they passed out on the couch. And then when her mom called she said not to move her, so now i'm stuck with no TV, no noise, no nothing. Only the stinking computer, and my sparkling apple cider, which is half gone already. 

Also: Yesterday i basically embarrassed myself at Nick's because i got sick and threw up on his carpet at his going away party. SWEET. I didn't even drink anything. I can drink like a tank and not have a hangover, but when i have a migrane, WATCH OUT! i may puke on you.

I'm working a lot this week, which means lots of dinero on my paycheck.
I got tickets to see Anberlin. YAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAY i love them. 
I'm also going to get tickets to see Cartel and Cobra Starship and Boys Like Girls, but they don't go on sale to the public for another two weeks, and i'm too lazy to get a credit card and buy them presale. 
Winterfest is on my 18th birthday, and i'm going to skip it and go clubbing with Dave, because winterfest is lame. 

I'll probably post later. LOVE

Youtube is addicting. Especially the shoes video and the muffin video. oh geez.

Yesterday we saw The Pursuit of Happyness, and it made me want to cry and it was super cute. Yea that's right...super flippin' cute.

Christmas is tomorrow! YAAAY!
So we went to mass tonight and there are these two girls who go to my church who sing well, but they have to sing louder and longer than everyone else to show it off. and at first i was like, whatever, they're good singers, but now it's really bugging me, because they do it only for attention. Ok, so you can sing...do you really have to rub it in everyone else's face?

I'm excited because I'm going to buy tickets to go see Anberlin (yaaaay i love them) and the tour with Cartel, Boys Like Girls, and Cobra Starship (all of whom i love as well). YAAAY another concert season...
But i'm pissed because i can't go see Dave play because I'm not quite 18. BOOOOO!! i'll be 18 just a measly 25 days later...but no. I can't go. SUCKY!


ALRIGHTY i'm off...Santa will be here soon and he'll be needing cookies...LOVE

Yearbook party was fun! lots of random questioning and catch phrase and more good clean fun. Then we drove home behind Christine at an average of 23mph (the speed limit was 55mph). EWWW then Wes almost died because he passed us both.
ALSO yesterday was a pretty sweet concert. TheAudition is always amazing, even when the crowd is completely bitchy (well get to that in a sec) and they play acoustic when they really didn't have to play at all. And the first band was crazy. Like, I've never seen a crowd more pumped for the first band. The lead singer jumped off the 12 foot speaker and crowd surfed. I've never seen ANYONE do that, let alone the first band. SO check out Madena Lake (sorry if that's spelled wrong or something). BUT THERE WAS ONLY ONE THING a lot of people in the crowd were really really ridiculous. For the record, I was sick and throwing up chicken nuggets (gross...sorry) and there were girls saying that I "couldn't handle it." (that's crap...thanks). and there was this kid who got all up in my face and another in a bandana who thought he was badass and another girl who blatantly pushed me in the back be cause i got in front of her. Whatever...concert drama is stupid. And it must have been good because i'm sore...HA whatever

Peanut Butter Jelly time will be forever stuck in my head.

Tomorrow starts Secret Santa Season...yeaaa! I better not get screwed over...

Tomorrow is also the 2nd concert of the 6 day concert season...Murder by Death. Also seeing the Format, AAR, MCS, and Boys Like Girls on Monday.  YAAAAAY.

The commercial with the Asian guy singing/rapping in the bathroom gets me every time. So does Tourette's guy. I know it's horrible and i'm sorry but it's hilarious.

OK im gonna go watch South Park now...LOVE

This is going to be a very emo post. I'm not usually emo, but that's the best word that's coming to mind right now.

So David and I have been very off and on over the past week or two, and I kept thinking about if i made a good desicion and if he was going to be alright and all that post-breakup madness, and I'm happy to say i made a good choice not to be with him, but that conclusion came with a whole hell of a lot of bullshit that hit me deep. I've been made fun of and I've been laughed at and all that cruel shit, but I haven't been this hurt by anything like that since middle school. Ugh. 

I'm happy the truth came out, and I'm happy it's final, I'm just sad at the way it happened. I wish it wasn't so messy.

Kay I'm done. I'll post happier things sometime soon.


LOVE

Ahhh the drama...
So in Applied economics, our company name was BAMF (business associates of marketing and finance...not the other thing you dirty thinkers...) and I kind of didn't think anyone was going to take us seriously, but whatever, i never really remember voting on the name. But anyways, it died. It didn't just get shot down, it got stomped on and spit on and it's legs broken with a sledgehammer. I'm in complete and utter shock (sarcasm). I mean if they don't accept BOOTY shirts, what makes anyone think they're going to accept THAT?! now we're all going to get competely bitched out by Mr. drabek, because he got bitched out for something he didn't even do, and something he thought had been approved, but actually hadn't. Thats not fair to him, or anyone for that matter.

I'm also having a serious problem with certain types of people also. I hate when people dress compeltely insane or do stupid shit or listen to a certain type of music because it's different, not because they like it, and then they look down on you because you're all "sheep," but really, they're sheep because they're following what they think is different for the sole purpose of looking like they have more class than you. I also hate when people namedrop, especially music. I also hate when people you thought were friends are actually stupid and bitchy. I hate when my boyfriend is sarcastic, and when all of my friends are sick and not at school. I hate when basketball practice is frusterating, and i hate my ankle. (WHEW...that was a load off).


Well that was fun! Other exciting things in mi vida:

DAVID GOT A RED CARD because he PUNCHED A KID IN THE STOMACH!! haha who even saw that coming? oh i love that kid

JNet is home this weekend!
Homecoming was badass...i wore striped tights!
Yesterday, Dee and Lindsey ran into each other. funniest basketball moment we've had so far...

Alrighty...more later when i feel like it.

So i'm a tad mad. ha that rhymed. i'm not at fucking arby's with the rest of my team because they decided to leave without me, but they told me they "looked everywhere" and called me and shit. Wow. i was in the training room the WHOLE FUCKING TIME. it's not like i'm going to wait outside for you in 50 degree weather with flip flops and a t-shirt on. show a little effort.

I think i put too much into the hope that people are trustworthy and will do the right thing, and I  open myself up a little too much, and its a huge letdown when they do something wrong to me. I give a lot, and don't get it back. all the fucking time.

I would say i'm gonna be positive now, but i'm just not having a good day. so i guess i'll just stop bitching and end it there. 

much Love

Currently I'm babysitting, and letting the boys watch cartoons they probably shouldn't be watching, but whatever. 
I've lived next door to them and for 2 years have not noticed that they have a trampoline...sweet jesus what i've been missing.

I've spent the past hour online looking at livejournals of lesbians who just so happen to also be obsessed with knitting.

AND OH MY GOD DAVID GOT A TATTOO!!!!! AND HE DIDN'T TELL ME ABOUT IT!!! he was just over last night and i look at his arm and there it is! i freaked out for like 10 minutes because i was so freaking excited. it says "alive" in icelandic and it's pretty sweet. But the best part of it is is that now i can walk up to him and be all "SWEET TAT MAAAAN" yea i'm stoked.
Then i was trying to convince my parents to let me get my nose pierced before i turned 18...that was probably the biggest waste of time. 

And my car is being ridiculous. All of a sudden it decided to throw a shit fit and have everything go shitty at once.
I've spent 185 bucks on two new (nice) tires, but now my oil is leaking, and the crack in the windshield is rapidly expanding. MEH.

Things That Are Making Me Happy:
1. David
2. The possibility of Clerks II with Katie and JNet tonight
3. The Mackin' Cheese on the Stove at the moment
4. I Got Paid Today, and it was more than i expected.
5. I'm also getting paid for babysitting twice today
6. I found more concerts i want to go to...yesss...
7. To be materialistic...new clothes

Things that are making me unhappy:
1. Drama
2. The mere thought of conditioning the rest of the week at 7 a.m.
3. The Paycheck i got (mentioned above) was only 48 bucks. ha.
4. The Keene's are taking over my life
5. I'm a tad broke
6. I have no idea what i want to do with my life and the idea of that is making me crazy...i mean you see all these kids who are my age or younger and they're successful doing what they love to do...whether it's make music or movies or golf or whatever, and hell, i don't have that kind of talent, or drive, or passion. It sucks.
7. The whole trend of everyone trying to be original, but actually they're all the same. Rarely do i see someone wearing what they want because that's what they like and want to wear. You'll always have your scenesters say they're doing it, but seriously, they all look the same to me. And they all give me (and Jnet when she comes) the same looks that we don't fit when we go to shows in Howell and stuff. GAH! that's what i say to that.

haha sorry i have a lot of pent up anger. Maybe i should get into boxing or something...

I guess i should leave now, since i've been randomly adding to this post for about 45 minutes between Mac making and eating and watching children and stuff.

On a final note: Jay and Silent Bob are sexy, and i am staging a protest against anime. Sorry David.

LOVE

Another Year, another Nationals. Same FT. Wayne, Different Coach, and a whole hell of a lot more drama.
Actually, there was a whole hell of a lot of drama. Egos clashed, Leaders who thought they were never wrong, that sort of shit.

I did go shopping...it was great. And i like a lot of the girls on the team. I think when you're with the same people for 4 days straight they tend to get on your nerves a tad.

Now David is coming over!! But two a days are coming this week, so if i freak out on someone, it's not your fault. For the Record
